### Task 2.1 — Dynamic Import `recharts` (via chart.tsx)
**File:** [chart.tsx](file:///c:/VamsiKrishna/Github/Tusker-managment/src/components/ui/chart.tsx)  
**Time:** 30 minutes · **Risk:** Low · **Score Impact:** +3 (Frontend) · **Savings:** ~80 kB

The [chart.tsx](file:///c:/VamsiKrishna/Github/Tusker-managment/src/components/ui/chart.tsx) imports `recharts` with `import * as RechartsPrimitive`. This pulls the entire library into the shared bundle since [chart.tsx](file:///c:/VamsiKrishna/Github/Tusker-managment/src/components/ui/chart.tsx) is likely re-exported from a barrel file.

**Strategy:** Make [chart.tsx](file:///c:/VamsiKrishna/Github/Tusker-managment/src/components/ui/chart.tsx) lazy-loaded. Any component that uses `<Chart*>` components should dynamically import them:

```typescript
// In any page/component that uses charts:
const { ChartContainer, ChartTooltip } = await import("@/components/ui/chart");
// OR wrap the chart section:
const ReportChart = dynamic(() => import("../_components/report-chart"), { ssr: false });
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] `recharts` does NOT appear in the shared JS chunk (verify via bundle analyzer: `pnpm analyze`)
- [ ] Charts still render correctly on report pages
- [ ] Other pages load without recharts code

