### Task 3.1 — Virtualize Kanban Columns with `@tanstack/react-virtual`
**File:** [kanban-column.tsx](file:///c:/VamsiKrishna/Github/Tusker-managment/src/components/task/kanban/kanban-column.tsx)  
**Time:** 3 hours · **Risk:** Medium · **Score Impact:** +5 (Frontend)

`@tanstack/react-virtual` is already installed (v3.13.13) but unused. Implement virtualization in the column scroll container:

```typescript
import { useVirtualizer } from "@tanstack/react-virtual";

// Inside KanbanColumn:
const parentRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);

const virtualizer = useVirtualizer({
    count: deduplicatedSubTasks.length + (hasMore ? 1 : 0), // +1 for sentinel
    getScrollElement: () => parentRef.current,
    estimateSize: () => 120, // ~120px per card
    overscan: 5,
});

// Replace the map with:
<div ref={parentRef} className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto ...">
  <div style={{ height: virtualizer.getTotalSize(), position: 'relative' }}>
    {virtualizer.getVirtualItems().map((virtualRow) => {
      const subTask = deduplicatedSubTasks[virtualRow.index];
      if (!subTask) return <LoadMoreSentinel key="sentinel" ref={loadMoreRef} />;
      return (
        <div
          key={subTask.id}
          style={{
            position: 'absolute',
            top: virtualRow.start,
            height: virtualRow.size,
            width: '100%',
          }}
        >
          <KanbanCard ... />
        </div>
      );
    })}
  </div>
</div>
```

> [!WARNING]
> **DnD integration:** `@dnd-kit/sortable` + virtualization requires careful coordination. The `SortableContext` must still receive all IDs, but only visible cards are rendered. Use `virtualizer.scrollToIndex()` to keep drag targets visible.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Only ~10-15 cards rendered in DOM per column (instead of all 50)
- [ ] Scrolling is smooth at 60fps
- [ ] Drag and drop still works between columns
- [ ] Infinite scroll sentinel still triggers load more
- [ ] No visual glitches during scroll

