### Task 3.3 — Normalize Kanban Board State
**File:** [kanban-board.tsx](file:///c:/VamsiKrishna/Github/Tusker-managment/src/components/task/kanban/kanban-board.tsx)  
**Time:** 2 hours · **Risk:** Medium · **Score Impact:** +3 (Frontend)

Currently Kanban state is `Record<TaskStatus, { tasks: Task[] }>` — updating one task copies entire arrays.

**Refactor to normalized structure:**

```typescript
// Instead of:
const [data, setData] = useState<Record<TaskStatus, { tasks: Task[] }>>(initialData);

// Use:
const [entities, setEntities] = useState<Map<string, KanbanSubTaskType>>(new Map());
const [columnIds, setColumnIds] = useState<Record<TaskStatus, string[]>>({
    TO_DO: [],
    IN_PROGRESS: [],
    // ...
});

// Moving a card between columns:
function moveCard(taskId: string, from: TaskStatus, to: TaskStatus) {
    setColumnIds(prev => ({
        ...prev,
        [from]: prev[from].filter(id => id !== taskId),
        [to]: [taskId, ...prev[to]],
    }));
    // Entity stays the same — no array copying!
}
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Moving a card between columns does NOT re-render cards in other columns
- [ ] Column counts update correctly
- [ ] Load more appends correctly
- [ ] Filter changes work as before

