## Risk Matrix

| Task | Risk Level | Rollback Plan |
|:---|:---|:---|
| 1.1–1.8 | 🟢 None | Git revert |
| 2.1–2.7 | 🟡 Low | Dynamic imports are backwards-compatible |
| 3.1 Virtualization | 🟡 Medium | Test DnD thoroughly; disable if broken |
| 3.3 Normalize State | 🟡 Medium | Keep old state shape, wrapper functions |
| **4.1 Middleware Auth** | **🔴 High** | Feature flag: `USE_EDGE_AUTH=true` |
| 5.1 Denormalized Counters | 🟡 Medium | Backfill script + migration rollback |
| 5.3 Redis Caching | 🟡 Medium | Fallback to direct DB on Redis failure |

---

## Deployment Strategy

```
Phase 1 → Merge to main, deploy immediately
Phase 2 → One PR per task, deploy individually
Phase 3 → Feature branch, preview deploy, test thoroughly
Phase 4 → Feature flag (USE_EDGE_AUTH), gradual rollout
Phase 5 → Staging first, production after 24h soak test
```

---

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **The three highest-ROI tasks that together deliver 60% of the score improvement are:**
> 1. **Task 4.1** (Middleware Auth Fix) — removes 280ms from every page load
> 2. **Task 2.1–2.7** (Bundle Reduction) — cuts JS from 401 kB to 160 kB
> 3. **Task 3.1** (Virtualization) — reduces DOM nodes from 300 to 30
>
> If you only have time for 3 tasks, do these.
